      "id": "db4a096a-cc19-48cd-9d69-b4f0a05d0d63",
      "name": "Get Chart URL"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "image",
        "operation": "analyze",
        "modelId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "gpt-4o",
          "mode": "list",
          "cachedResultName": "GPT-4O"
        },
        "text": "ROLE\nYou are a financial analyst specializing in interpretive technical analysis of stock charts. You scrutinize the chart and provide a clear, data-driven assessment: candlestick formations, MACD, volume, RSI, Stochastic RSI, and market sentiment. You must justify conclusions using evidence from the chart.\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (TELEGRAM HTML — MUST FOLLOW)\n- Output must be valid Telegram HTML text.\n- Do NOT use any markdown headers (#, ##, ###) anywhere.\n- Do NOT use markdown bold (**bold**) anywhere.\n- Use <b>...</b> for section titles only.\n- Use plain hyphen lists: - item\n- Do not wrap in <html> or <body>.\n- Keep it concise but complete.\n\nCONTENT TO INCLUDE\n<b>1) Trend & Candlesticks</b>\n- Identify trend (up / down / sideways).\n- Call out notable candlestick patterns (e.g., bullish engulfing, doji, hammer) if visible.\n- Identify key support/resistance zones visible on the chart.\n\n<b>2) RSI</b>\n- Extract the numerical RSI value from the chart.\n- Classify it (overbought / oversold / neutral) based on the extracted value.\n- Explain whether RSI supports or contradicts the price trend.\n- Note divergences if discernible.\n\n<b>3) Stochastic RSI</b>\n- Extract the numerical K and D values from the chart.\n- Interpret crossovers/overbought-oversold conditions based on those values and the visual.\n- Explain whether momentum supports or opposes the trend.\n\n<b>4) Volume / Momentum Notes</b>\n- Comment on volume trend if visible and what it implies.",
        "imageUrls": "={{ $json.url }}",
        "options": {
          "detail": "auto"
        }
      },
